England on 591-6 Against India at Lunch, Led by Ian Bell’s Double Century

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-20T12:09:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-20/bell-pietersen-lead-england-to-457-3-in-final-cricket-test-against-india.html
Ian Bell ’s double century helped
 England  reach 591-6 at lunch on day three of the final cricket
Test against  India .  Bell scored a career-best 235 before being caught leg
before wicket by Suresh Raina.  Ravi Bopara  is 44 not out and
Matt Prior has scored 18.  Sree Sreesanth has taken three wickets for India and Raina
has claimed two.  England leads the four-match series 3-0 and has guaranteed
its place as the No. 1 team in the International Cricket Council
Test rankings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  